# Comment Functionality Documentation

## Overview
The comment system enhances interactivity by allowing users to leave comments on blog posts. Authenticated users can post, edit, and delete their comments, fostering community engagement.

## Features

### 1. Comment Creation
- Authenticated users can post comments on any blog post
- Rich text formatting support
- Character limit: 1000 characters
- Real-time character counter

### 2. Comment Display
- Comments are displayed in chronological order (oldest first)
- Each comment shows:
  - Author's avatar and username
  - Time since posting (human-readable format)
  - Comment content with formatting
  - Edit/Delete options (for authors and staff)

### 3. Comment Management
- Authors can edit their own comments
- Authors can delete their own comments
- Staff users can moderate all comments
- Comment editing history is tracked

### 4. Comment Moderation
- Comments marked as `active=True` are visible
- Inactive comments are hidden (for moderation)
- Staff users can manage comment visibility

## Models

### Comment Model
```python
class Comment(models.Model):
    post = models.ForeignKey(Post, on_delete=models.CASCADE, related_name='comments')
    author = models.ForeignKey(User, on_delete=models.CASCADE)
    content = models.TextField()
    created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)
    updated_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now=True)
    active = models.BooleanField(default=True)